      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Progressive trotter SUNSET HILL NZ (1) has shown terrific ability in his four Australian starts so far, winning three times at Menangle and pushing wonder mare Keayang Zahara when beaten just 2.2m into second in the Group 1 The Great Square in Brisbane in December. Gets the ace draw for his return and was readied with a nice trial. Last season's Great Southern Star winner WATTS UP PARTYTIME (7) was up to his old tricks when he broke at Melton last start but beat Sunset Hill when winning a trial since. He was a first up Menangle winner two back and is big on talent when on his game. French import KRISTAL JOSSELYN (5) is the big query. Hasn't raced for more than 10 months but is talented and has been trialling strongly, winning his last three hitouts at Menangle. RAKERO BLAZE NZ (3) led and faded last start but was a city winner prior so can be prominent from a low draw.",
